2.5.04	Added the cnEcSet method to the following control classes:			cnwdad1 13/08/2002
		
			o Button
			o CheckBox
			o ComboBox
			o Frame
			o GroupBox (also inherited by the Sheet class)
			o Label (also inherited by the ProgressBar class)
			o ListBox
			o OptionButton
			o Picture
			o ScrollBar
			o StatusLine
			o TextBox
		
		This method will update the receiver's text, caption, listIndex, picture or boolean
		value with the specified parameter value.
		
		Added the CnEcExceptionForm, a subclass of CnExceptionForm.			cnwdad1 13/08/2002
		
		Added the cnEcIsBaseException() method to the Exception and			cnwdad1 13/08/2002
		CnEcBaseException classes to indicate whether an exception was raise by BaseSchema.
		
		Added the following method to the BaseSchema (Application) class:	cnwdad1 13/08/2002
		
			o cnEcXHandler(pTheException:Exception):Integer;
		
		This method is a general global exception handler which deals with BaseSchema exceptions.
		If the exception was raised by BaseSchema, then an error message box will display the
		error, otherwise the CardSchema unhandled exception dialog will be shown.
		
		Added the cnEcShowDialog method to the Exception class.  This		cnwdad1 13/08/2002
		method will display an error dialog box which will show the error message.
		
		Added the following method to the Global class:						cnwdad1 14/08/2002
		
			o cnEcFindTranslatableString(pIsCaseSensitive:Boolean; pAllStringNames:StringArray io);
		
		Searches through all Translatable Strings (in the current locale) for a string entered by
		the user.
		
		Added extra checks for the kind of ExplicitInverseRef when updating cnwdad1 26/08/2002
		the manual side of an inverse reference.
		
		Changed the CnEcXMLNoidSelect form to sort the listbox of names.	cnwdad1 26/08/2002
		
		Added the following methods to the Global class:					cnwdad1 02/09/2002
		
			o cnEcIsUnix():Boolean;
			o cnEcGetFileSeparator():Character;
		
		The first method returns a boolean flag to indicate whether the operating system of the
		platform on which the calling node is running is Unix.  The second method determines the
		platform of the operating system on which the calling node is running, and will return
		the appropriate file name separator, i.e. a "\" (for Windows) or "/" (for Unix).
		
		Added the following methods to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 02/09/2002
		
			o cnEcIsValidFileName():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsValidPathName():Boolean;
		
		The first method will validate a Windows OS file/directory name.  Note that the name must
		not include the full path name - each node in the path must be validated individually.
		The second method validates a Windows OS file/directory path name.
			
		Fixed a problem with the CnEcNumericBox class where, if the Layout	cnwdad1 18/09/2002
		was type Integer, the text was still defaulting to "0.00".
		
		Added the setAlignment() method to the following BaseSchema			cnwdad1 19/09/2002
		controls:
		
			CnEcCurrencyLabel
			CnEcNumericLabel
			CnEcCurrencyBox
			CnEcNumericBox
		
		The controls' default alignment (right-aligned), can be overridden by subclassing the
		control(s) and reimplementing this method.
		
		
		Improved up the Object::cnEcExceptionDetails() method to provide	cnwdad1 19/09/2002
		more information, and better presented.

==========================================================================================
2.5.05	Fixed the CnEcRateGraph::delete method.								cnwdad1 08/10/2002
		Hot Fix #249 for JADE 5.2.08 now deletes child controls automatically - where developers
		have implemented destructors on controls to explicitly delete child controls, an error 4
		exception is raised.
		
		Added the following methods to the Binary primitive:				cnwdad1 10/10/2002
		
			o cnEcClearBit(pIndex:Integer) updating;
			o cnEcIsBit(pIndex:Integer):Boolean;
			o cnEcSetBit(pIndex:Integer) updating;
		
		These methods can be used for setting and fetching and clearing a flag within a bit-mask.
		
		Added the "splitType" attribute to the CnEcSplitContainer class.	cnwrs1 16/10/2002
		This attribute determines what method is used on a resize of the container to move the
		splitter bar.  It can be set to one of the following class constants:
		
			SPLITTYPE_RATIO		: The size of the left and right panes are adjusted to maintain the same ratio.
			SPLITTYPE_LOCKLEFT	: The size of the left pane is fixed and the size of the right pane is adjusted.
			SPLITTYPE_LOCKRIGHT	: The size of the right pane is fixed and the size of the left pane is adjusted.
			
		For LockLeft and LockRight there is a minimum size which the variable pane won't get
		adjusted less than.  If this size is reached the fixed size pane will be resized.  If the
		user subsequently resizes the control so that the fixed pane can be shown at its set size
		it will be.
		
		Changed the windowCreated method of the CnEcSplitContainer class	cnwdad1 16/10/2002
		to set the background color to Window.Color_3DFace, instead of just "Gray".
		
		Added the following method to the App class (BaseSchema):			cnwdad1 22/10/2002
		
			o cnEcIsBaseException(pTheException:Exception):Boolean;
		
		This method can be used to determine whether an exception object is a BaseSchema exception.
		
		Modified the BaseDocModel application to allow a list of classes	cnwdad1 01/11/2002
		(and their properties) to be specified in an XML document.  This list is optional, and if
		not specified, then all schema classes and properties will be documented as before.  Other
		changes include the addition of a Header and Preface page that accompany the index pages.
		The major changes were to the following methods:
		
			o global::cnEcDocumentModel(pTheParameter:CnEcDocParameter):String;
			o Class::cnEcDocumentSelf(pTheParameter:CnEcDocParameter; pAllDocProperties:CnEcDocModelPropertyByNameDict; pDirectory:String; pSchemaColl:SchemaColl; pPathToIndex:String);
		
		These methods also have changes to their signatures.
		
