		Changed the CnEcTimeBox control so that if the time setting is		cnwdad1 26/11/2002
		either null or is not valid, then the control's time will be reset to midnight.
		
		Changed the CnEcScrollBox control so that if the control is 		cnwdad1 27/11/2002
		read-only then the values cannot be scrolled.
		
		Added the following method to the Class class:						cnwdad1 20/12/2002
		
			o cnEcCount(pWhereClause:String; pIsSubclasses:Boolean):Integer;
		
		This method can be used to return a count of all instances of the receiver, optionally
		executing JADE code against each object, such as some condition to include or exclude
		particular objects in the count.
		
		Fixed the Date::cnEcIsWeekDay() method which was returning true if	cnwdad1 20/12/2002
		the receiver was NOT a week day.
		
		Added the following method to the Date primitive:					cnwdad1 06/01/2003
		
			o cnEcIsLeapYear():Boolean;
		
		This method will return a boolean flag to indicate whether the receiver is a leap year.
		
		Changed the CnEcCalendarSelectForm.txtYear control's readOnly		cnwdad1 13/01/2002
		property to false.
		
		Fixed a bug in the CnEcFindClassForm::findClass method (for the		cnwdad1 14/01/2003
		JDBrowser application) where a null object exception occurred if the entered class name
		was not found.
		
		Modified the following controls to invoke the firstChange() event	cnwdad1 23/01/2003
		method the first time the text value is changed.
		
		o CnEcDateBox
		o CnEcTextBox
			o CnEcScrollBox
				o CnEcTimeBox
		
		Whenever the text value is (re)set (using either a set method or the pop-up calendar for
		the Date Box), the firstChange() event method will again be invoked the next time text
		value is changed.
		
		Fixed a bug in the CnEcXmlParser::extractTag() method so that field	cnwdad1 23/01/2003
		instance objects will also be checked for attribute values.  Previously only group instance
		objects were being checked.
		
		Modified the Global::cnEcDocumentModel and associated entities to	cnwdad1 23/01/2003
		add the ability to specify an alias for a class or property in the XML of the class
		input file.  The new format of the XML to specify which classes, properties and methods
		to document is as follows:
		
			&lt;Class name="class name" alias="alias name"/&gt;
			
			and/or:
			
			&lt;Class name="class name" alias="alias name"&gt;
				&lt;Property name="property name" alias="alias name"/&gt;
				&lt;Method name="method name" alias="alias name"/&gt;
			&lt;/Class&gt;
		
		Added the following methods to the Integer primitive:				cnwdad1 24/01/2003
		
			o cnEcIsAltKey():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsCtrlKey():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsShiftKey():Boolean;
		
		These methods return a boolean flag to indicate whether the ALT, CTRL or Shift key is
		pressed respectively.  The methode assume that the receiver is the value of the "shift"
		parameter of various GUI object event methods, such as the keyDown, keyUp, mouseDown,
		mouseMove and mouseUp events.
		
		Modified the Class::cnEcDocumentSelf method to include the name of	cnwdad1 24/01/2003
		the superclass in the heading of the HTML page.
		
		Added a check to the Object.cnEcMonitor method for the length of	cnwdad1 27/01/2003
		the monitor message.  The maximum allowable length of userInfo data is 48k.
		
		Changed the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method to only document the	cnwdad1 27/01/2003
		properties and methods that are specified in the XML class file.  Previously, if no
		properties or methods were specified for a class, then *all* properties and methods were
		documented.  As before, if no XML class file is used, then all classes and their properties
		and methods will be documented.  Also added a hyperlink to the class's superclass.
		
		Changed the String::cnEcDecodeWebData() method to handle the cases	cnwjha1 30/01/2003
		where 1) the last character is a %, and 2) where a percent is followed by invalid data,
		we need to skip to the next percent, not convert the first pair of numbers we come to.
		
		Changed the signature of the File::cnEcSetOpenName method to		cnwdad1	31/01/2003
		include a parameter for file extension filters.
		
==========================================================================================
3.0.01	Added a feature to change the background color of the following		cnwdad1 05/02/2003
		controls when they get the focus:
		
			o CnEcCheckBox
			o CnEcComboBox
			o CnEcListBox
			o CnEcOptionButton
			o CnEcTable
			o CnEcDateBox
			o CnEcTextBox
		
		The desired background color can be defined on the Properties dialog in the Painter.
		
		Added the isIncludeClassText attribute to the CnEcDocParameter		cnwdad1 07/02/2003
		class to control whether or not class text is included in the documentation.
		
		Changed the BaseDocModel application to not generate a hyperlink	cnwdad1 19/02/2003
		to a class that is not included in the documentation.  This includes property types
		and the class being inherited from.
		
		Changed the property::cnEcDocumentSelf() method to not print		cnwdad1 21/02/2003
		property text if the option on the doc. parameter object to include class text is not set.
		
		Added the "isMinimumZero" property to the CnEcScrollBox control.	cnwdad1 25/02/2003
		When true, the scrollbox cannot be scrolled to a value of less than zero.  Using this
		property avoids the need to set specific maximum/minimum values.
		
		Fixed the Global::cnEcDocumentModelHeadings method where the JADE	cnwdad1 25/02/2003
		and product logo file names didn't require the "..\" prefix in the HTML.
		
		Added the following methods to the TimeStamp primitive:				cnwdad1 27/02/2003
		
			o cnEcMillisecondsSince(pStart : TimeStamp) : Decimal;
			o cnEcEstimatedEndTime(pStartTime:TimeStamp; pTotalParts:Integer; pPartsDone:Integer):TimeStamp;
		
		The first method will return the number of milliseconds since the pStart parameter. The
		second method returns the estimated time when a job/processing will complete.
		
		Changed references to the CNEC_SYSTEM_COLOUR global constant to		cnwdad1 28/02/2003
		instead use the Window.getSystemColor() method.  This affects the following custom
		controls:
		
			o CnEcDateBox
			o CnEcDisplayPanel
			o CnEcLine3D
			o CnEcSplitContainer
			o CnEcTextBox
		
		Fixed a problem where the CnEcBrowseButtons control's destructor	cnwdad1 03/03/2003
		was not unsubscribing for collection notifications when the control was deleted.
		
		Changed the BaseDocModel application form to default the top/		cnwdad1 12/03/2003
		bottom schemas to the current schema, and to default the output directory to the
		Windows TEMP directory.
		
		Changed the BaseSchema::cnEcXHandler method to report BaseSchema	cnwdad1 12/03/2003
		exceptions with a dialog box, instead of showing all of the exception details.  If the
		exception is not a BaseSchema exception, then the handler will pass back to the next
		one in the stack.
		
		Added checks to the BaseDocModel application to check for duplicate	cnwdad1 12/03/2003
		Schemas, Classes, Methods and Properties.  If a duplicate is detected, then a BaseSchema
		Exception will be raised.
		
		Fixed a bug in the BaseDocModel application where a File object		cnwdad1 12/03/2003
		was not being deleted after the XML Class Input file was parsed, thus causing a leak and
		leaving the disk file locked if an exception was raised.
		
		Added the following class constants to the Control class:			cnwdad1 13/03/2003
		
			o CNEC_LEFT_CLICK (value=1)
			o CNEC_RIGHT_CLICK (value=2)
			o CNEC_MIDDLE_CLICK (value=3)
		
		The values of these constants corresponds to the value of the "button" parameter in event
		methods such as "mouseUp" and "mouseDown".
		
		Added the following methods to the Array class:						cnwdad1 22/03/2003
		
			o cnEcRandomSelect(pMaxSelect:Integer) updating;
			o cnEcScramble() updating;
		
		The first method randomly selects the specified maximum number of candidate elements from
		receiver, and discards the remaining elements.  The second method randomly scrambles the
		order of the receiver's elements.
		
		Changed the Binary::cnEcClearBit() and Binary::cnEcIsBit() methods	cnwdad1 03/04/2003
		to check for whether the pIndex parameter exceeds the maximum possible bit index.
		
		Added the following method to the Class class:						cnwdad1 18/04/2003
		
			o cnEcGetAllMethods(pAllMethods:MethodSet io);
		
		This method will populate the specified Method Set with all of the receiver's methods,
		plus all methods inherited from all superclasses.
		
		Added the following methods to the CnEcArray class:					cnwdad1 03/06/2003
		
			o includesBinary(pBinaryValue:Binary):Boolean;
			o includesString(pStringValue:String):Boolean;
		
		Changed CnEcSpellCheck::checkProse method to store words to ignore	cnwdad1 03/06/2003
		from a StringArray to type CnEcArray to handle prose with words longer than 60 characters.
		
		Fixed a bug where the CnEcBackSchedTask's reschedule options were	cnwdad1 17/06/2003
		not being correctly set up on the CnEcTaskDetailsForm.
		
		Fixed a bug where the background color of the CnEcTextBox was not	cnwdad1 17/06/2003
		being reset when the control's readOnly property was changed from true to false.
		
		Fixed a bug in the CnEcScrollBox::selectFieldNumber method where	cnwdad1 17/06/2003
		the "self.selLength := ..." line of code was commented out, causing the scrolling of
		the field value to become corrupted.  Changed to be conditional on whether the control
		is read-only.
		
		Fixed a bug in the CnEcSpellCheck::checkProse method where, if the	cnwdad1 18/06/2003
		last word in the prose was being corrected, then the last character in the word was
		always appended to the end, and hence the original text was ALWAYS updated even if
		the user cancelled the check (because the appended character caused the prose to
		appear to have been altered).
		
		Changed the CnEcBackSchedManager::createTask() method to return the	cnwdad1 18/06/2003
		newly created CnEcBackSchedTask (subclass) object.
		
		Added a click() event method to the CnEcDateBox control to handle	cnwdad1 18/06/2003
		the cursor being positioned using the mouse, and to still skip over the separator
		characters.
		
		Changed the CnEcCalendarSelectForm to populate the Month combobox	cnwdad1 19/06/2003
		in reverse order so that when it's scrolled, it does so in the same direction as the year
		scrollbox.
		
		Changed the CnEcCalendarSelectForm so that when a new year is		cnwdad1 19/06/2003
		keyed in, pressing the Enter/Return key will update the calendar.
		
		Changed the CnEcCalendarSelectForm to handle the user keying in a	cnwdad1 19/06/2003
		new year, and then clicking on another control and still have that year recognized on
		the lostFocus event of the Year control. Because the Calendar Control's click event
		occurs before the Year control's lostFocus event, we need to pick up the year from
		the Year control in the Calendar Control's click event.
		
		Added the following new control subclasses:							cnwdad1 25/06/2003
		
			o CnEcDockBar (JadeDockBar)
			o CnEcDocContainer (JadeDockContainer)
			o CnEcEditMask (JadeEditMask)
			o CnEcDateMask (CnEcEditMask)
			o CnEcRichText (JadeRichText)
		
		Changed the CnEcReleaseHistoryForm::doFormLoad method from using a	cnwdad1 31/06/2003
		BaseSchema method to fetch the server timestamp, to use the native method.
		
		Changed the CnEcReport::getDefaultParameterValue method from using	cnwdad1 31/06/2003
		a BaseSchema method to fetch the server timestamp, to use the native method.
		
		Changed the CnEcReport::setCurrentTimeStamp method from using a		cnwdad1 31/06/2003
		BaseSchema method to fetch the server timestamp, to use the native method.
		
		De-implemented the following methods:								cnwdad1 31/06/2003
		
			o app::cnEcGetServerComputerName
			o app::cnEcGetServerTimeStamp
			o global::cnEcGetServerTimeStamp

==========================================================================================
3.0.02	Added a validatation check to the CnEcTaskDetailsForm form to		cnwdad1 01/10/2003
		prevent a schedule date prior to the current date.
		
		Changed the CnEcMonitor form to no longer use a foreach to iterate	cnwdad1 01/10/2003
		the nodes and processes because this left a timing hole where other nodes/processes
		could be locked out.
		
		Added the following method to the ListBox class:					cnwdad1 02/10/2003
		
			o cnEcSetObjectSelected(pObject:Object);
		
		Sets the selected item of the ListBox at the index that contains the specified object.
		
		Added the following method:											cnwdad1 21/11/2003
		
			o cnEcFirstToUpper():String;
		
		This method can be used to capitalize a string, without the need to be called from an
		updating method, or to declare local variables to manipulate constant" values.
		
		Changed the CnEcBackShedTask::setCompletedTimeStamp method to that	cnwdad1 09/02/2004
		parameters 4 to 6 that are sent to the createTask() method send local property values
		instead of just a false value.
		
		The following methods have been moved from Global to App - any		cnwdad1 15/03/2004
		references to them have been changed accordingly:
		
			o alert
			o beep
			o isValidObject
		
		Added the following method to the Date primitive:					cnwdad1 31/03/2004
		
			o cnEcWeekOfMonth():Integer
		
		This method will return the week number of the receiver's month.
		
		Added the following method to the Integer primitive:				cnwdad1 31/03/2004
		
			o cnEcGetColorRatios():String
		
		This method will return a string with details of the percent of Red/Blue/Green for
		the receiver (assuming that the receiver is a valid RGB value).
		
		Fixed the Class::cnEcDocumentSelf method to generate a relative		cnwdad1 14/04/2004
		hyperlink to a class that is inherited from (i.e. to a superclass), allowing the
		documentation files to be copied to different locations without breaking the integrity
		of the hyperlinks.
		
		Changed the SchemaEntity::cnEcDocumentGetClassHyperlink to only		cnwdad1 14/04/2004
		return a hyperlink if the class in question is actually included in the documentation,
		otherwise only the class name will be returned.
		
		Fixed was a problem where, when running the BaseDocModel			cnwdad1 14/04/2004
		application, thin clients would get a 1008 exception because the karma.dll library is
		not in the client's binaries directory. The application will no longer default the
		target directory with the Windows' "temp" directory.
		
		There is a bug in JADE where the Class::name meta object returns	cnwdad1 14/04/2004
		the wrong property reference when setting the name of a DynaDictionary key - this has
		been temporarily resolved by coding the literal name instead. The methods affected are:
		
			o CnEcDocParameter::create
			o GBaseSchema::cnEcDocumentModel
		
		Fixed a bug in the CnEcDateBox::lostFocus method. Locale			cnwdad1 14/04/2004
		overrides (i.e. on app server) are not supported by JADE.  Changes in JADE 6 to enforce
		this caused layout problems when parsing for current locale set the the date property.
		Changed the method to now just use the "cnEcDate()" method.
		
		Reinstated the default value of the "temp" directory method for the	cnwdad1 19/04/2004
		BaseDocModel application.  The method which fetches the directory name now uses a new
		native method instead of relying on the karma.dll library.
		
		The signatures of the following methods on Global was changed due to the CnHttp::cnGetFile
		method in CardSchema having been changed:
			o cnEcGetHttpBinary
			o cnEcGetHttpFile

==========================================================================================
3.0.03	Added a boolean flag, called isExactMatch, to the					cnwdad1 04/06/2004
		CnEcWildcardSearch class.  By default, if a search string does not have a wildcard
		character on the end, an asterisk is appended so that all strings that are longer
		than the search value will still match - setting the boolean flag to true will mean
		that this will no longer be the case.  For example, by default, if the search string
		is "ach", then a word such as "achromatic" will still match, but if the boolean flag
		is set to true, then only the word "ach" will match.
		
		Changed the CnEcCsvFile::cnEcLoadCsvFile method to (1) Prevent		cnwjub1 17/08/2004
		and exception 4030 when attempting to calculate percentNowDone if the file length is
		less than 100 characters, and (2) Include the record terminator string length when
		calculating partsDone.
		
		Changed the following two methods on the String primitive:			cnwdad1 24/09/2004
		
		o cnEcEncodeWebData
		o cnEcEncodeWebDataAndStripCrLf
		
		A change in JADE 6.0.9 means that the value of the "stringLength" variable is now only
		evaluated at the beginning of the foreach loop, hence the resetting of the variable's
		value within the loop is now ignored.  Now using a while loop instead.
		
		Changed the Exception::cnEcGetDetails() method to also report the	cnwndl 24/09/2004
		position in the method where an exception occured (if the position is &gt; 0).
		
		Changed the CnEcAgent::agentExceptionHandler method so that when	cnwdad1 17/10/2004
		storing Exception::errorItem in the self.lastError property, if errorItem is null, then
		fetch the errorText and store that instead.
		
