    <GlobalConstant name="CNEC_SYSTEM_COLOUR" id="e54ff617-ca2f-40ce-b3e8-fe4238759b87">
        <category name="Literals"/>
        <source>#80000000</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>When referencing the JADE Window class color constants, the actual
color values as defined by the user in their desktop settings are
the values being used.  This color may vary between different
users and may also be dynamically changed.  To set a color value
so that the actual color used will always be the current value set
by the user in the desktop settings, set the high bit of the
Window class color constant to true.

This constant has only the high bit set - add the value of this
constant to any JADE Window class color constant for the required
system color.  For example:

begin
	label1.backColor	:=	label1.getSystemColor(Color_ActiveCaption);	// The actual color value.
	frame1.backColor	:=	SYSTEM_COLOR + Color_ActiveCaption;			// The dynamic color value.
end;</text>
    </GlobalConstant>
