    <GlobalConstant name="HCS_Version" id="867958a4-c7bf-4b1f-a96e-5fdf4e69df01">
        <category name="HostConnectivityConstants"/>
        <source>"2.00.01"</source>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>Changes 


Version 2.00.01
	- Upgraded to run under Jade version 4.0


Version 1.00.05
   - Installed boolean flag to indicate that the retry timer has been set
     This is so that after consecutive connection closes for different dialogues
     each won't start the timer - which can screw things up


Version 1.00.04
   - fixed timerEvent on TCPLINCConnection class so that we will now
     reset the timer that tracks queueItems when connection is 'dropped'
     after not receiving a response from a doalog for 5 minutes


Version 1.00.03
  - removed text from Linc system entitiy structures
  - changed to TCPLincConnection exception handling to only pick up TCP connection errors -
    rather than all connection errors


Version 1.00.02
 - trylock code put around delete of IspecToHost.  The delete was pulled out into a 
   separate method.
 - now closing connection after 5 minutes if no response has been received from the host 
   after an ispec has been sent to it.
 - reworked Configure form so that a field can be protected (set from an option in the
    .LNC file)

Version 1.00.01
 - initial 'release'</text>
    </GlobalConstant>
